1 September 2016The registration for set-top-boxes is gaining traction. This Saturday on the 3rd of September 2016, Minister of Communications, Ms Faith Muthambi, will lead a Broadcasting Digital Migration public awareness campaign to inform community members of Mtititi Village, LIM 345 Local Municipality, in Limpopo about the registration process for set-top-boxes (STB s). We started in the Northern Cape in the Square Kilometre Array (SKA) last October in the core towns of the SKA. Installations of STB s is now at 98% in those towns, soon we will revisit the Northern Cape SKA areas to announce switch-off date. We are making progress , said Minister Muthambi.As part of this visit, Minister Muthambi will oversee the registration of community members qualifying to receive the Government-subsidised set-top-boxes, which will enable them to enjoy a superior television watching experience. Details of the event: Date: Saturday, 3 September 2016 Venue: Mtititi Thusong Service Centre Hall Time: 8:30 RSVPs: Thanyani Netshikweta on 072 459 3153Enquiries: Mish Molakeng Cell: 082 469 3997 Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of the Ministry of Communications